Letter Count I

Have the function LetterCountI(str) take the str parameter being passed and return the first word with the
greatest number of repeated letters. For example: "Today, is the greatest day ever!" should return greatest
because it has 2 e's (and 2 t's) and it comes before ever which also has 2 e's. If there are no words with 
repeating letters return -1. Words will be separated by spaces.

Examples
Input: "Hello apple pie"
Output: Hello

Input: "No words"
Output: -1

Resposta

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

public class LetterCountI {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Testes de exemplo
        String str1 = "Hello apple pie!";
        String str2 = "No words";
        System.out.println(letterCountI(str1)); 
        System.out.println(letterCountI(str2)); 
    }

    public static String letterCountI(String str) {
        String[] words = str.split("\\s+");
        String result = "-1";
        int maxRepeats = 0;

        for (String word : words) {
            int repeats = countRepeatingLetters(word);
            if (repeats > maxRepeats) {
                maxRepeats = repeats;
                result = word;
            }
        }

        return result;
    }

    private static int countRepeatingLetters(String word) {
        int[] letterCounts = new int[26];
        word = word.toLowerCase().replaceAll("[^a-z]", "");

        for (char c : word.toCharArray()) {
            letterCounts[c - 'a']++;
        }

        int maxRepeats = 0;
        for (int count : letterCounts) {
            if (count > 1) {
                maxRepeats = Math.max(maxRepeats, count);
            }
        }
        return maxRepeats;
    }
}   
